---
import MainLayout from '../../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
import Link from '../../components/Link.astro';
import TableOfContents from '../../components/TableOfContents.astro';
const title = 'Rotors Shader - Cities Skylines Modding';
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import { images } from '../../data/imageImports.js';
---

<MainLayout title={title}>
	<TableOfContents />
	<section class="pt-12 pb-48 text-lg sm:ml-64 xl:mr-64 text-hit-gray-500">
		<h1 id="overview" class="pb-8 text-4xl font-bold border-b-4 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400">
			Rotors Shader (Props & Buildings)
		</h1>
		<div class="content">
			<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="about">
				<a href="#about" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>About</a
				>
			</h2>
			<div class="flex flex-col gap-6 mt-4 lg:flex-row">
				<div class="lg:w-2/3">
					<p>
						Unlike regular shaders, the rotors shader supports semi-transparency, therefore it can be used for transparent
						glass, fake water, or anything else that requires semi-transparency.
					</p><p class="mt-4">
						It's usually used for props, buildings, and building sub-meshes which are a part of a bigger asset, such as a glass
						windows sub-building for a normal building.
					</p><p class="mt-4">This article assumes you are familiar with regular prop and building asset creation.</p>
				</div><div class="lg:w-1/3">
					<a href="/images/shader/rotors-transparent.jpeg" target="_blank">
						<Picture
							width={images.rotortransparent.width / 2}
							densities={[1.5, 2]}
							formats={['avif', 'webp']}
							src={images.rotortransparent}
							alt="Rotors shader used for glass and fake water"
							class="w-full h-auto"
							loading="eager"
						/></a
					><p class="explanation">Rotors shader used for glass and fake water.</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="limitations">
				<a
					href="#limitations"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing.">Limitations</a
				>
			</h2>
			<h3 class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500" id="lighting">
				<a href="#lighting" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Lighting</a
				>
			</h3>
			<p class="mt-4">
				Rotors shader doesn't receive shadows from other objects, meaning it will look unnaturally bright when in the shadow. Also,
				it only receives illumination from the sun, therefore it will be black when facing away from the sun, which is why it's
				recommended to use a dark diffuse texture.
			</p>
			<h3 class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500" id="shadows">
				<a href="#shadows" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Shadows</a
				>
			</h3>
			<p class="mt-4">
				The shadows for semi-transparent parts will not be semi-visible, they will only be fully visible when the opacity is above
				50% (128 on alpha map) and invisible below that.
			</p>
			<h3 class="pb-4 mt-16 text-2xl font-semibold border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-500" id="reversed-render-order">
				<a
					href="#reversed-render-order"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Reversed Render Order</a
				>
			</h3>
			<p class="mt-4">
				This means if you have multiple faces on top of each other, the furthest one will render on top of the closest one. This is
				not very obvious if the object is highly transparent. If the object is split into multiple props, buildings, or sub-meshes
				which are far enough apart then it won't have this problem.
			</p>
			<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="script">
				<a href="#script" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Script</a
				>
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-4">
				To change the shader of your prop, building, or sub-mesh to rotors, you need to run <Link
					classes=""
					href="https://gist.github.com/ronyx69/20070de77a0dc02fb669be0ff5365eb4"
					text="one of these scripts"
					theme="externallink"
				/> using the <Link
					classes=""
					href="https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=450877484"
					text="ModTools"
					theme="externallink"
				/> console <span class="key">F7</span>.
			</p>
			<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="mesh">
				<a href="#mesh" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Mesh</a
				>
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-4">
				There's nothing different about the mesh compared to regular assets, but it's possible to use the vertex color red channel
				to control the opacity, although for almost all cases using the alpha texture makes more sense.
			</p>
			<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="textures">
				<a href="#textures" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Textures</a
				>
			</h2>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="diffuse">
				<a href="#diffuse" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Diffuse</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Works like any diffuse texture.</p>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="alpha">
				<a href="#alpha" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Alpha</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Controls transparency, white is fully opaque, black is invisible, shades of gray are semi-transparent.</p>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="color">
				<a href="#color" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Color</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Rotors shader only uses the first color variation, so it's not very useful.</p>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="illumination">
				<a
					href="#illumination"
					title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing.">Illumination</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">
				The illumination is unusual and looks different based on time of day. For buildings, remember to import a black illumination
				map, as it will default to a light gray (192).
			</p>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="normal">
				<a href="#normal" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Normal</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Works like any normal map.</p>
			<h4 class="pb-4 mt-8 text-xl font-medium border-b text-hit-gray-400 border-hit-gray-950 lg:mt-12" id="specular">
				<a href="#specular" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Specular</a
				>
			</h4>
			<p class="mt-4">Works like any specular map.</p>
			<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="lod">
				<a href="#lod" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing.">LOD</a
				>
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-4">The rotors shader doesn't work for LOD models.</p>
			<div class="flex items-start justify-start gap-2 mt-6">
				<svg
					xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
					xml:space="preserve"
					class="w-8 h-8 text-hoverlink flex-shrink-0 fill-hoverlink"
					viewBox="0 0 32 32">
					<path
						d="M16 4C9.4 4 4 9.4 4 16s5.4 12 12 12 12-5.4 12-12S22.6 4 16 4zm0 22c-5.5 0-10-4.5-10-10S10.5 6 16 6s10 4.5 10 10-4.5 10-10 10zm0-12c-.6 0-1 .4-1 1v6c0 .6.4 1 1 1s1-.4 1-1v-6c0-.6-.4-1-1-1zm0-4c-.6 0-1 .4-1 1s.4 1 1 1 1-.4 1-1-.4-1-1-1z"
					></path>
				</svg>
				<p class="italic">
					<em>
						You can use <Link
							classes=""
							href="https://steamcommunity.com/sharedfiles/filedetails/?id=922939393"
							text="the Transparency LODs Fix mod by TPB"
							theme="externallink"
						/> to increase the render distance of the main models.
					</em>
				</p>
			</div>
			<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="examples">
				<a href="#examples" title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing."
					>Examples</a
				>
			</h2>
			<p class="mt-4">
				You can download the source files of some example assets, which use rotors shader for some parts of the asset.
			</p>
			<div class="mt-4 content-download">
				<Link
					classes=""
					href="https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/0B6Ccf1N5h5f7cmwzd09MdE9nQkk?resourcekey=0-0aM4mUa7xZyYB6KZqqAsvg&usp=sharing"
					text="Apple Store Fifth Avenue"
					theme="downloadbutton"
				/>
			</div>
			<div class="mt-4 content-download">
				<Link
					classes=""
					href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B6Ccf1N5h5f7ME5xbUpTR2NFNUU/view"
					text="Pools"
					theme="downloadbutton"
				/>
			</div>
			<div class="mt-4 content-download">
				<Link
					classes=""
					href="https://drive.google.com/file/d/0B6Ccf1N5h5f7b3FIYUZvUHRJbjg/view"
					text="Bauhaus Dessau"
					theme="downloadbutton"
				/>
			</div>
		</div>
		<!-- ?Video Section -->
		<h2 class="pb-8 mt-24 text-4xl font-medium border-b-2 border-hit-gray-600 text-hit-gray-400" id="relevant-videos">
			<a
				href="#relevant-videos"
				title="Click to generate a direct link to this section in the browser's address bar for easy sharing.">Relevant Videos</a
			>
		</h2>
		<ul class="text-lg mt-4 text-hit-gray-500 list-inside">
			<li>
				<h3 class="mt-4" id="rotors-shader">
					<Link href="https://youtube.com/watch?v=ELoMC1rWOSc" theme="youtube" text="Rotors Shader" classes="" />
				</h3>
			</li>
		</ul>
	</section>
</MainLayout>
